ariba.util.expr
Class DynamicSubscript

java.lang.Object
  ariba.util.expr.DynamicSubscript

public class DynamicSubscript
extends Object

This class has predefined instances that stand for special "dynamic subscripts" for getting at the first, middle, or last elements of a list. In such expressions, these subscripts look like special kinds of array indexes: [^] means the first element, [$] means the last, [|] means the middle, and [*] means the whole list.

Author:
Luke Blanshard (blanshlu@netscape.net), Drew Davidson (drew@ognl.org)
